Canadian Stocks Decline After Energy Producers Reverse Gains

-- B y   S t e p h e n   K l e e g e
-- 
2011-03-07T16:14:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/canadian-stocks-decline-after-energy-producers-reverse-earlier-gains.html
  Canada ’s main stock index erased a
gain and fell for the first time in four days as energy shares
reversed an earlier rally.  The Standard & Poor’s/TSX Composite Index slid 59.02
points, or 0.4 percent, at 11:06 a.m. in Toronto after rising as
much as 0.5 percent. Potash Corp. of Saskatchewan Inc. led the
decline, falling 2.4 percent to C$57.95  Suncor Inc., Canada’s biggest oil and gas company, fell 0.2
percent to C$46.28 after climbing as much as 1.5 percent
earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
